Abstract

Introduction

Yam production in Nigeria is one of the largest agricultural produce (Prez-Flores et al. 2017). Knowing the nutrient composition of litter is useful for planning nutrient management of plantations (Bai et al. 2022). In Cocoa (*Theobroma* *cacao* L.) plantations, tree species are combined in different vertical strata (Fontes et al. 2014; Prez-Flores et al. 2017). Cocoa litter has a poor quality Fontes et al. (2014) reported N rate in cocoa litter was low .
